Expand Malwarebytes page with in-depth Privacy VPN content

Adds two new sections to /malwarebytes-premium/ answering "what does
the VPN actually do, and what does changing your country mean":

- /03 YOUR PRIVATE VPN: plain-English explainer + 6 benefit tiles
  (public Wi-Fi safety, ISP can't watch, WireGuard 256-bit ChaCha20
  encryption, hides IP/rough location, kill switch, audited no-logs).
- /04 CHANGE YOUR COUNTRY: how choosing a server location works, an
  honest everyday example (reaching your own UK accounts abroad), an
  "An honest word" callout (VPNs aren't magic, banks may flag a new
  location, we won't promise it unblocks Netflix/iPlayer), plus a
  "Privacy VPN at a glance" spec checklist.
- 3 new FAQs (VPN vs antivirus, streaming honesty, no-logs) + richer
  "what is the VPN for" and device/platform answers; these flow into
  the FAQPage schema automatically.

All facts verified via a research+adversarial-verify pass against
official Malwarebytes sources (WireGuard-only, 256-bit ChaCha20,
150+ servers / 60+ locations incl. UK London, Windows/Mac/Android/iOS,
strict no-logs independently audited by X41 D-Sec in 2026, desktop-only
kill switch). Uses the accurate product name "Malwarebytes Privacy VPN".
Honest caveats baked in: no streaming-unblock promises (Netflix/iPlayer
T&Cs), VPN is not antivirus, location-change isn't guaranteed.

